                            tbamud-rwb README (doc/)
                            ------------------------

tbamud-rwb is a from-scratch reimplementation of TbaMUD (a CircleMUD/DikuMUD
derivative) in the Rust programming language.  These docs are adapted from the
stock TbaMUD `doc/` tree to describe how the *Rust* rewrite actually works.
Where stock TbaMUD documents C internals, autoconf, or in-game OLC editors that
the rewrite does not (yet) implement, the corresponding file here says so
plainly instead of describing machinery that isn't present.

The authoritative top-level docs live in the repository root:

  ../README.md   - build & run instructions (cargo), command-line flags, tests.
  ../LICENSE.md  - license (derivative of TbaMUD / CircleMUD / DikuMUD).

Building & running
------------------

There is no `configure`, Makefile, or per-platform build procedure.  The
server builds with Cargo on any platform with a Rust 1.75+ toolchain and a C
`libcrypt` (for DES password hashing):

    cargo build                 # debug   -> target/debug/circle
    cargo build --release       # release -> target/release/circle
    cargo run -- -p 4000        # run on port 4000 (default)
    telnet localhost 4000

The compiled binary is named `circle` (CircleMUD convention) and reads its data
from a `lib/` directory, exactly like the C server.

Command-line flags (`-p -d -r -m -s -o -c -q`) are documented in ../README.md.

Documentation index (this directory)
-------------------------------------

Content / gameplay:
  files.md        - the lib/ data tree as the rewrite uses it.
  color.md        - the `@` color-code system (rwb uses `@x`, not `&` or raw ANSI).
  socials.md      - socials and the socials.new format.
  building.md     - world-data file formats; how to edit the world (by hand).
  act.md          - how the rewrite sends messages to players (no C `act()`).
  msgedit.md      - the combat/skill messages file.
  dg_events.md    - DG Scripts: which trigger types the rewrite supports.
  ProtocolSystem.md - telnet/protocol support (basic; no MSDP/GMCP/MXP).
  porting.md      - using stock CircleMUD/TbaMUD world data with the rewrite.

Administration / operations:
  admin.md        - running, configuring, and maintaining a rewrite server.
  syserr.md       - log / SYSERR-style messages and what they mean.
  debugging.md    - debugging the Rust server (RUST_LOG, lldb/rust-gdb).
  testing.md       - the `cargo test` unit-test suite.
  utils.md        - the C utility programs and their rewrite status.
  releases.md     - versioning / where the changelog lives.
  license.md      - pointer to the adapted ../LICENSE.md.
  FAQ.md          - frequently asked questions, adapted for the rewrite.
  coding.md       - Rust coding conventions for contributors.

Obsolete C build guides (README.UNIX/WIN/MSVC*/BSD/CYGWIN/OS2/VMS/AMIGA/ARC/
BORLAND/WATCOM/CMAKE): these described compiling the C server on specific
platforms/toolchains.  The rewrite builds uniformly with `cargo`, so each of
those files now contains only a short note redirecting here.

Getting help
------------

The original TbaMUD community lives at The Builder's Academy (telnet
tbamud.com 9091).  For the rewrite specifically, the code, parity log, and
issue surface are this repository.
